5. Store user accounts:
	* Use a third-party authentication service, such as Auth0 or Firebase, to handle user authentication and account creation. These services offer pre-built authentication components and APIs that you can use in your Next.js app.
	* Alternatively, you can use WordPress itself to handle user accounts. WordPress has built-in user authentication and registration functionality that you can use via the REST API.
